Combining more than three components, or using any tool on a combined item, tends to drastically reduce its value. The 'mutation catalyst' also seems to create negative value items. Aim for a three-component, grown, amphibious flying hybrid for the highest score.

Combining two 'grown' items (especially those sharing an environment or with 'land' and 'air' features) often creates a valuable hybrid. Applying the growth serum *once* to a *grown combined item* can result in a 'super-grown' item with increased value, but applying it a second time to make it 'ultra-grown' drastically reduces its value. The mutation catalyst consistently led to negative item values in my experience, so use it with extreme caution or avoid it entirely. Also, combining two already combined items resulted in a very low, negative value.

message: Prioritize using the Growth Serum on ALL initial ingredients; it reliably increases value and adds the 'grown' feature. Avoid the Mutation Catalyst and re-applying the Growth Serum to an already 'grown' item, as these actions consistently decreased value in my experience. The most effective strategy for high scores is combining 'grown' ingredients from different habitats (land, water, air). Start by combining two items from distinct habitats, then add a third to create a highly valuable multi-habitat hybrid. Once you have a high-value hybrid, it's often best to submit rather than risk further modifications or combinations with remaining low-value items.
